    "algorithms that keep taking the highest immediate raw revenue ad without considering future decay",
    "algorithms that reason per area instead of across the full schedule",
    "algorithms that overuse one advertiser too early",
    "algorithms that ignore long-term opportunity cost from repeated advertiser usage"
  ],
  "rewards": [
    "balancing strong same-advertiser ads with diversified moderately strong ads",
    "understanding that early repeated use of one advertiser weakens later placements",
    "global revenue reasoning across all areas and time slots",
    "careful packing that preserves high-value slots for the right advertiser mix"
  ],
